kjots (version 0.3.0) - a note taker
------------------------------------

NOTE:
If you upgrade from a version _before_ 0.2.2:
 Edit your .kjotsrc file and remove the last ',' at the
 end of the lines:
 Folders=item1, item2,
                     ^ - remove it !
 Hotlist=item1, item2,
                     ^ - remove it !

You need:
- qt 1.33
- kdelibs 1.0 or newer

What to do:

See the installation instructions for kdeapps.

this will install:

$(KDEDIR)/bin/kjots
$(KDEDIR)/doc/HTML/kjots/
$(KDEDIR)/doc/HTML/kjots/kjots.html
$(KDEDIR)/apps/Utilities/
$(KDEDIR)/apps/Utilities/Kjots.kdelnk
$(KDEDIR)/lib/pics/jots.xpm
$(KDEDIR)/lib/pics/filedel.xpm
$(KDEDIR)/lib/pics/OpenBook.xpm

How to configure:

If you don't get the icons in the toolbar then check
your config files .kderc or .kde/config/kjotsrc

You need a valid entry like:
[KDE Setup]
IconPath=$KDEDIR/lib/pics:$KDEDIR/lib/pics/toolbar

Kjots will create a valid entry if it is missing. But if
there is already such an entry it won't change it.
